The paper deals with the use of dynamic state estimation for monitoring and control of power grids, with a focus on mitigating risks from cyber attacks and unknown inputs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category, which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. The paper also mentions the use of attack detection algorithms and optimization frameworks, which are common in the Cybersecurity (cs.CR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of real-time measurements and the potential incompleteness of power system models, which are relevant to the Cyber-Physical Systems (cs.CY) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) categories. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CY, and cs.SE, in that order.
